<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146841>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Maximum likelihood phylogenetic tree of polymastiid species reconstructed from 28S rDNA (C-region). Values> 70 of the bootstrap support for the clades are indicated above the branches. Below branches in italics Bayesian inference posterior probabilities ≥ 0.95. The species sequenced in this studied are highlighted in boldface. Scalebar depicts substitutions /site." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146841/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146843>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Radiella nidula sp. nov. A. The holotype QM G337524 on deck immediately after collection, upper surface up. B. The holotype QM G337524 fixed basal surface. C. Scanning Electron Microscope collage of a cross section through the paratype QM G337532. D. Bouquets of intermediate tylostyles in the basal surface of the paratype QM G337524. E. Exotyles from the basal surface. F. Closeup of ends of the style in E. G. Intermediate tylostyles in the main body of the sponge. H. Ends of the tylostyles in G. I. Small tylostyles from the body of the sponge." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146843/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

